{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "29", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "14", "M": "34", "S": "35"}}, "news": [{"title": "Shriram Properties targets \u20b93,750-4,000 crore pre-sales in FY27, expects Pune to overtake Chennai", "para": "Shriram Properties expects to clock \u20b93,750-4,000 crore of pre-sales in FY27 and remains on track to meet its FY28 targets, said Murali Malayappan, chairman & managing director, and Gopalakrishnan J, executive director & CEO, Shriram Properties. The company plans to deepen its presence in Bengaluru, Chennai, Pune and Kolkata, while evaluating Mumbai and selectively looking at office, data centre and rental housing opportunities.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/shriram-properties-aims-for-4000-crore-pre-sales-by-fy27-pune-to-surpass-chennai/131387232?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-79874/131387232.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "PPCB flags compliance gaps, urges builders to follow EC norms in Zirakpur", "para": "The Punjab Pollution Control Board (PPCB) met with the Builders Welfare Association in Zirakpur to emphasize environmental compliance and adherence to Environmental Clearance (EC) conditions. Officials urged builders to display guidelines on-site, accurately self-file applications, and prepare for monsoon by cleaning rainwater harvesting systems and ensuring efficient STPs for sustainable urban growth.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/ppcb-urges-compliance-from-builders-in-zirakpur-for-environmental-protection/131388698?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-81310/131388698.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Hyderabad's Raidurg area witnesses a record-breaking land auction as one acre fetches \u20b9237 crore", "para": "Hyderabad's Raidurg witnessed a record-breaking land auction as one acre fetched Rs 237 crore, significantly surpassing previous benchmarks. Gowra Ventures Pvt Ltd secured the 6.29-acre parcel for IT and mixed development. This phenomenal price, 70% over the reserve, underscores investor confidence in Telangana's burgeoning economic landscape and Hyderabad's prime real estate appeal.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/historic-237-crore-per-acre-land-auction-in-hyderabads-raidurg/131386238?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-189632/131386238.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}